    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Set-based implementation using unordered_set. O(1) to construct and O(visits) to advance.</para>
<para>Vector-based implementation using a versioned byte array. Faster for <ref refid="structfaiss_1_1FAISS__FINAL_1a98d84ffe67f14cb991ea206a04e9d90d" kindref="member">get()</ref>/set(), but O(size) to initialize. <ref refid="structfaiss_1_1FAISS__FINAL_1ae8a9f65e7b9663f08ddbdf7d818493ea" kindref="member">advance()</ref> is O(1) except every 250 calls, which are O(size). </para>
    </detaileddescription>
